caption: Cool place.
Love everything about this place
Everything is delicious with top notch ingredient quality and warm superb service. Great wine offering, an edited lunch menu, and an extremely well orchestrated, sunny outside dining situation.

I love to explore new coffee shops and support local business so when I saw this place I was excited to try specially because they have a cute outdoor seating.  I like to drink coffee after lunch ( not morning) so I went to 4 Horsemen since is very close to my job sadly I didn’t like the coffee , too bitter not nice aftertaste , I asked for an americano but looks like and tasted like French press which is my last favorite. Be sure to ask how they make the coffee before ordering .

This is by far the best restaurant in Williamsburg with outstanding staff, constantly evolving dishes, and a revolving and rotating selection of wine. The key to this review is that the chefs have the ability to provide outstanding, exceptional, and constantly evolving food which is hard to find on a reliable basis in New York.

12 / 10 consistently. Staff is interested and caring, don’t know what kind of wine you like? The staff has answer for exactly what you need. I’ve never had a dish that wasn’t perfect and amazing; sometimes with some interesting surprises. Like the celery salad with a bit of mint and hint of spice, delicious. If you don’t come here you are missing out.
Fantastic food, great wine, very good service. Hard to get a table most of the time but worth it!

Although the dishes are tasty and interesting, the service is a bit strange. You feel unwelcome there. I’ve been twice and although I really wanted to like this place, The atmosphere is cold and the portions are incredibly small for the price. More overhyped than quality. The wines are also overhyped and mediocre.
Hands down, one of the best culinary experience I've ever had.
Wonderful customer service, great drinks and side dishes. Super fan of this place!
Super thoughtful wine selection, Great small plates to pair, and just a fun fun space with obviously great music. GO with friends, on a date, whenever

If you’re into natural or bio wines you have to come here. It’s a bit pricey but worth every sip. The dishes are really thoughtful, seasonal and satisfying. I’ve been for a solo glass, birthdays, dates, honestly can’t go wrong. Attention to detail on everything from food, to service, cutlery, glasses. It’s all SO good!
Very Good

Our meal started with the Lady Edison Ham. We could taste the bristly hairs of the pig, the mud it rolled in, and the forest air it breathed. The spinach malfatti made its cousin the gnocchi jealous with its delicate outer texture and melty insides. And the arugula salad's soft, thin-sliced manchego provided a pillow for the interspersed pickled eggplants spiking up the fresh greens. A diverse and well-curated wine list so you couldn't make a mistake.  A sublime experience.
Williamsburg’s best local wine bar! Incredible staff, you’ll be in safe hand.

The outdoor dining setup here is one of my favorite I've seen in the city this summer. The tables are very well spaced out and away from people walking by on the sidewalk. The team's precautions are also top notch - minimal interaction and they ask you to wear a mask during those interactions, wines poured in the restaurant, one person allowed for the restroom at a time. Brunch here was delicious as always!
(Translated by Google) A divine meal !!! I will go again soon  (Original) Una comida divina!!! Volveré a ir pronto
They did a great job adapting to outdoor service. Food was amazing and service impeccable.

The wine is pretty good.. tried 4 different types ...clearly tipey atm from here but a great time . The food waa pretty amazing as well the corn, spaghetti and fries is what i had and waa pretty amazing.. would highly recommend... make a reservation and go!

Without any doubt, this is one of the best places to dine in the world. Anything Nick touches just tastes delicious, he really knows how to make the best of each ingredient. Wine selection is one of the best in the US. Billy will help you get what you want, even if you don’t know what you’re looking for... The vibe is just the best. Even in current outdoors arrangements the acoustic of this place is simply perfect.
Excellent food. Outdoor dining.

I had heard good things but when I got here, the reception was really cold and uppity. There were several empty tables outside and I was told I would be called to be seated within 45 minutes. That call never came. Had a much more jovial time at several other spots around the area and definitely will not try here again.

Love The Four Horsemen for weekend brunch! They post their brunch set menu on Fridays so you can see in advance what you'll get for $32. I've been 2 weekends in a row and several times before and they've hit it out of the park each time. Bright, rich flavors, surprisingly filling portions, and variety of dishes. There's also always a cool selection of wine available. I'd suggest going before 1pm in order to avoid waiting for a seat. Highly recommend!
One of the better dining experiences I've had in a while.

Bread was good wine was good  The yellow fin tuna was not edible. I literally took two bites because it wasn’t fishy in a fun fancy way. Tasted old and I don’t want to get sick. Still had to pay for it... never again.

Once you come here you just want to keep coming back. Wine list amazing, for bottles and glasses. Food for sharing truly great and different. It has an amazing atmosphere, lighting, music, all top notch. The waiters are extremely qualified and know a lot about not only the menu but also about wine. It is definitely something to be done once in Brooklyn.

It is a lovely small restaurant with vibrant atmosphere. I like the food here, creatively designed, smartly seasoned and beautifully presented. The chef understands complexion of savory and also emphasizes the true flavors of the ingredients. I enjoyed their seafood and sausage most. The flatbread is a little bit below the bar. The only thing I may complain is it is too small. I felt compressed when dining. Since it has limited number of tables, I suggest reservation before visiting.
my go to neighborhood spot! Solid rotating wine list, and bread and butter is to die for! you’re doing yourself a disservice if you skip it.
Very good brunch and excellent wine list.

This place is amazing! We discovered it by chance and were pleasantly surprised by our experience. They offer a menu and wine selection which is different from a regular restaurant, and that adds to the experience. Plus, the staff is great, walking you through the dishes and which wine goes better with the meals.
Incredible. Food, service, ambiance all on point...with an amazing natural wine list, to boot.

An intimate space with engaging staff. Warm bread with its accompanying stick of butter was a highlight, along with the dry aged ribeye (pictured). Reservations for normal times can be hard to get, it seemed like the bar seating area was first come first served however.

Came here on a Sunday afternoon for a drink and dessert. There were plenty of available tables but for some reason we were made to wait at the standing bar. When I tried to move over an available bar stool, I was scolded and told to put it back, despite the fact that another couple right next to us had stools at the standing bar. It took another 10 minutes for us to order a drink, which averaged $20 for a glass of wine. Once stools opened up at the main bar we finally got to sit down. I will give them that the olive oil cake with pistachio cream was good, but the attitude and service of this place is in definite need of improvement.
Delicious food and wine
Small plate was delicious and flavorful. Wine was awesome. Staff were courteous.
The best ! Friendly cool and an icon

It was a very cosy little neighbourhood restaurant with a decent wine collection. However, I was a bit surprised that it has a Michelin star because the food came across as tasty but not particularly memorable or creative. Great for a casual lunch/dinner!
Really great experience at a high end restaurant. Would definitely recommend.
one of best natural wine lists in NY and best staff especially lisa!!!
Great natural wine bar, and everything we ate was super delicious
Excellence.
Had the most fabulous time here. Amazing food, wine, service, vibes, etc.
Great pre fixe lunch. Excellent wine selection and service
Surely worthy of the star, and some

Without a doubt the best night you are going to have in NYC. Not only is the food incredible but the people and their passion for what they do is unmatched. No surprise that this restaurant received its Michelin star!
Outstanding!

Great  place to drink wine. Nice people who care about what they're doing.  Food was done very nice. clean ,fresh ingredients, tasty and the portion size was more then satisfying.  The wine list is huge with lots of options. We sat at the bar with Matt ,who was extremely knowledgeable about wine. If your in the willy B this should definitely be on your list of to go places

(Translated by Google) Great wine bar, very good food. The service is lovely. New York prices though!  (Original) Super bar à vins, très bonne cuisine. Le service est adorable. Prix new yorkais cependant !

Simply amazing. Four Horsemen is that rare wine bar that transports you to another world, somewhere in Paris, with incredible food, great service and the best of vibes. Come for the extensive natural wine list, filled with small organic winemakers around the world, and stay for the Japanese/French fusion plates. The warm bread, cultured butter is some of the best bread I’ve ever had. Other highlights include the endive salad, crispy potatoes, and butter beans.
Natural wine fan? Come here at The four Horseman. Great food, Awesome drinks.
Some of the best wine and food I’ve had in the States if not the world.  The sommelier was outstanding and recommended some beautiful and interesting wines.
Great atmosphere. Staff were nice.
Everything is great! The food, the wine and the service. Wow!

Wow, amazing little spot in Williamsburg that beats out most of the good spots in the city.  Food, wine, service all were top notch.  Kudos to clearly a very well run operation.  Look fwd to revisiting.
attentive services, lovely wine selection, tasty food! We loved it!
Awesome wine bar with exceptional food. They have one the best wine lists in NY (mainly european wine). It is small so make sure to book your table or just have glass of wine at the bar.
The customer service was just splendid. Incredibly helpful and the wine was just lovely!
Great food the cod fritters wow. Great wine list and cozy spot. Gets really busy with long wait make reservations

Unfortunately I had to change my review from last year. I had given 5 stars last summer but this time everything was just disappointing... The flavors and the quality of the dishes is not the same. We were 4 people and none of us enjoyed the meal. The staff was very friendly though.  This was my review from last year: During my 3 month stay in New York, this is definitely one of the best meals I had. A great dedication and incredible flavors in all dishes. The staff was very friendly and the music selection was just perfect.
Doesn’t get much better. The wine, food, service, atmosphere is simply outstanding. Finally got to sample the lunch and it was out of this world. I’ll be back, again and again.
Amazing food, interesting wine selection, and super friendly staff
Great wine selection. Knowledgeable staff. Awesome sound system and music.
Best bread ever.
Loved this place, their service is excellent and the dover sole is to die for. Try the chicken liver pate too. Amazing wine selection

Lovely wine bar! They’re busy even on Sunday so do reserve in advance, but walk-in are entertained and seated at the bar. Great wine by the glass options and the food was just crazily good. We ate some of our best plates here! The staff were very knowledgeable and helpful if you need some recommendations. Everyone was great and made all the difference! We had a great experience!
Amazing food and really lovely and knowledgable staff. Every dish was a banger.

Came for the name, and that it was my birthday. Place was a delight, the wine was tasty but the food especially the raw plates (beef, tuna, mackerel) - Oh my God! They were superb. Yes, it's expensive, but definitely worth a treat if in town.
(Translated by Google) Great food, wines and service!  (Original) Buenísima comida, vinos y servicio!
Great atmosphere and service, pork chop, tuna and bread were delightful.

Everything on the menu sounds really delicious on the page, so it's a challenge to avoid over-ordering. Luckily each dish tastes as good as it sounds, so even if you over-order you'll be glad you did. Highly recommend the yellowfin tuna and beef tartare, two stand-out dishes that should not be missed!

Came here last night with 2 friends. Very romantic and intimate feel. The menu wasnt intimidating and very short. The food was quick to come out and everything had strong distinct tastes but not overwhelming. Highly recommend this spot. We selected the 5 or 6 apps that cost less than $20 and it was all superb. Lastly the bread and butter is perfect.
Go for the staff, stay for the food, leave without learning anyone’s name. Just perfect.

First and foremost, 4H has the most amazing staff in the business. Everyone is funny, smart, engaging, attentive and damn do they know their wine. Seating is tight, but the food and incredible wines available here are well worth the wait. The people here are amazing, so check any bad attitudes at the door... You'll be rewarded
Amazing food, extensive wine list, knowledgeable staff. Our group included two vegetarians who found plenty of options to eat.
Great find!! Really enjoyed the food.  Excellent service
Food looked good

Came here on a Friday night for dinner. The plates are good - however the portions are small and way overpriced. We paid $120+ for 4 small plates and left hungry (we had to complete our meal at a nearby spot). Moreover, while most of the staff seemed fine, our waitress was not friendly to us. Overall, it felt like very little value for money. Would not recommend, except maybe for just a drink.

We stumbled in here by accident, but boy did we feel cool for doing so. This is a very hot spot, with great wine and food. The waiter was really nice, we had some good orange wine, the chicken liver, and the best lamb I think I've ever had. We happened to squeeze in and get two seats because we were there a little early, but I'd recommend planning ahead.
Amazing as usual and the wines are always impressive!
Killer wine list. Love a good natural wine bar!
Great wine bar to either end or begin your evening. Would recommend for a date as well.
Loved this place - tiny but didn't feel crowded, even when full.  Food was fantastic, wine list is extensive and the staff is friendly and knowledgeable. Highly recommend.
All dishes were well prepared and flavorful. Mushroom toast was a bit pricey at $20 for one piece of toast. Favorite dish was the raw scallop. Impressive wine list.

Little corner restaurant with fixed lunch menu - quality of the food is excellent, fresh and cooked to perfection. The chef is super nice, I feel like I wanna become friends with him when I go. He will recommend any type of wine you feel like drinking as they have an interesting selection.  Love it!
It was full when we arrived, but we were pleasantly greeted right away. Wine was great too!
Cute wine and eatery. Selection of nature wines. They offer a fairly set lunch menu.
Great atmosphere, great wine. Easy n nice.
Great place to get wine and some small plates.  Staff is very friendly and accommodating.  Good vibe to go along with good food and wine.

Found! Warm and welcoming to all who come, even on a busy Saturday night. The vibe is comfortable neighborhood bar/restaurant with a great wine list (no hard alcohol) and amazing creations coming out of the kitchen. Hard to pin down the menu of mostly small plates, but there is something for everyone. For more great review of the New & Authentic visit TheLoupe!
Always on point.

Food is very good and delicious. The service was good. We had an orange wine for the first time and it was very interesting, they let us taste a few different wines so we don’t get disappointed. Really liked the atmosphere as well.
Very good food. They fit a group of 7 in. Large wine list that includes orange wines. Chicken liver mousse was amazing and that's not really my thing. Also the endive salad.

(Translated by Google) Typical NY restaurant, popular with locals, not touristy. Absolutely recommendable, very good quality food. I was in the company of friends, we had dinner at the bar, gourmet recipes. Great wine. Party atmosphere, suitable for groups but also for couples. Thanks for the service, qualified staff.  (Original) Ristorante tipico NY, frequentato da residenti, non turistico. Assolutamente raccomandabile, cibo buonissimo e di qualità. Ero in compagnia di amici, abbiamo cenato al bancone del bar, ricette gourmet. Ottimo vino. Ambiente festaiolo, adatto per gruppi ma anche per coppie. Grazie per il servizio, personale qualificato.
Standing room only, but delivers on its popularity with its access to hard-to-finds.
The serve and food are absolutely amazing!  Great people,  great food and order the bread!!!
#vegetarianfriendly restaurant, very #cozy, great for #datenight
The portions couldn't be smaller. If you are a normal couple, the guy will get out hungrier than he came in. After spending $200+ I had to go to another place to eat... Ridiculous
Amazing food and service
Insane wine list for a place so tiny - be sure to make a res otherwise you will feel like you're in a mosh pit in the front. Every waiter is a somm with their wine knowledge.
Yup.
For a small spot the wine list is incredible.  The food is fresh, tasty and prepared beautifully.  The service is spot on; friendly and helpful.  A solid option when you're in Williamsburg.

High quality ingredients and wines - one of the few bars serving #naturalwine in the area. Expensive small plates but a nice experience. Would recommend coming for brunch instead of dinner. #datenight #cozy

I love this place! Incredible food, great service AMAZING WINE LIST! Everyone was so friendly and unpretentious. You do not have to feel shy asking questions about the wines. We went after my graduation and they even offered to put my flowers in water in the walk in <3 so thoughtful.
Short but tasty menu. Service was okay but the lobster mushroom polenta and wine made up for it
Knowledgeable staff,  slick pharaoh sanders tunes, tremendous endive salad.  Five stars.

My favorite restaurant in that part of the world. Great food, great wines, great team (you were so nice with my kids), great music and great location !  Guys, please open « les Quatre Cavaliers » in Paris !  Love you
Utterly fantastic
St Anselm was my favorite, till now
Just superb food service and wine. Dinner with friends was great.
Great place, great food and wine. Gets pretty busy.
This place is a gem! I loved yellowfin tuna and cantabrian anchovy dishes. The tables are quite small but the ambience is very romantic- perfect for a date.
Don't pass this place up in Williamsburg great wine great food
Didn't blow my mind....but food was pretty good
Excellent small plates, wine and service!
good drink selection

Delicious food and very accommodating staff. We turned up quite late at night without a reservation and they found us a table. It's not cheap, but as a special night out, this is romantic, fine dining. Would definitely come back if I was local.
Intimate and hip, a great place to take a date or hang with a friend over an eclectic wine list with matching share food dishes. Very, very friendly staff.
Favorite restaurant in NYC. Everything is delcious
Nice wine selection. Small plates are good to share.
pretty much the gold star of wine bars.
Our family had a great time. I highly suggest calling in a reservation for parties larger than 4. Great food and staff
Great food, average wine
The wine and staff are awesome! Don’t be afraid to ask questions...
Quaint, cozy wine bar - great pastas and appetizers. Difficult to get in; expect a wait, even for just two people.
Pricey but wondrous selection of natural wines and great food (with slight Japanese tilt). Raw fish is great here, whether it be of the crudo or sashimi variety. Get there early for a bar seat.
Amazing great food and service !!!!

Spectacular natural wine bar and restaurant in Williamsburg with a an eclectic list. Owned by James Murphy of LCD Soundsystem. Definitely get the bread and butter, beef tartare, dried skate wing, and pork chop. Small place which fills up fast so get there early.
100% recommend.
Fantastic wine bar with an excellent staff
Awesome wine selection
Tiny, but very cozy. Can take time to get the table. Food was interesting... it’s a wine bar after all

Went here with my girlfriend on a Saturday night around 10. They sat us immediately, given we didn't have a reservation it was quite a pleasant surprise. The waitstaff was also very kind. And outside of the cabbage, the meal and wine were over priced and frankly, just not that good.  We waited 20 minutes before someone came to give us our wine. I understand it is a busy night, but I could touch both walls at the same time. It's a tiny place. And I saw 3 workers in the bar at one point.  The wine was honestly just bad. I've had organic wine before. This just wasn't good wine. The Riesling and the Pinot were just lacking any unjoyable flavor profile.  The bread and butter was tasty. Great crunch, and warm. The butter was really good too. It was also $8 dollars for 3 small pieces of bread. And another $8 for 5 mussels. This was pretty tasty too. They also served 5 mussels. I'm from New York. I get how expensive things can be. I also get that sometimes you get bent over a barrel.  The oysters were outright gross. Weird texture, kind of felt like if you purposely tried drying the oysters like you would with beef. But then stopped half way to remember you shouldn't do that to fish.  The one bright spot was the cabbage. For all the plates and money we spent, spending time praising the cabbage almost seems like I'm doing a disservice.  The mackerel, bass and clam toast were fine and uninspiring. The clam toast tasted fine, but it was  poorly cleaned and had some grit. And all were poorly portioned for their price. Essentially all were mediocre and unmemorable.  Sounds like a lot of people enjoyed this place before me. Unfortunately, I experienced mediocre to bad food (minus the cabbage), awful wine and a terrible wait for pretty much everything.  Don't let Brooklyn LCD fans persuade you to like this place just because they want to. 4.7 stars is just a crime. There is no way this place should be reviewed this highly when you have gems like Aska in the neighborhood. Listen, I've done it too. You like something, you go in with Rose colored glasses bc "ZOMG LCD!". I get it. Unfortunately, I don't get how this many people are getting taken for a ride.

One of my favorite natural wine bars in the city, great food, excellent wine list and usually the music is ok too. Beautiful interior, killer soundsystem Billy is a gem and the rest of the staff are as well, great service 💯🍷🍾🥂
Great people, huge wine selection, amazing food.
(Translated by Google) Fantastic food, highly recommend the mangalitsa and the gnocchi!  (Original) Fantastic food, highly recommend the mangalitsa and the gnocchi!

Came here for my anniversary this past weekend. Mackenzie was fantastic. Wine was superb. This place is small, but it was an amazing night. Recommend this place if you truly appreciate creative small plates and some incredible wine. Cheers to the staff @fourhorsemenbk
Great food and great wine selection. Not thrilled with their "wait in line at the front" method of doing seating but the staff is pretty accommodating and that makes up for it.

Very chill wine bar in a cool neighborhood. Good selection of unusual/uncommon wines that are constantly rotated. Wish they had a little more by the glass and considered doing tasting flights, but that doesn't seem to be a thing in NYC. Service was great.
Natural wine bar with delicious food. Great date place.
Great food and wine, every single time.

Four Horseman is REALLY one of those places that makes me wish I could go 4.5, or GOOG used a scale to 10, because it's almost amazing and for sure better than a 4 out of 5.  The food? Tiny menu, and everything was GREAT. The wine list? Intimidating, but the young lady who helped REALLY helped and we had a great bottle at merely a high price.  But:  It's too loud, a bit dark unless you have GREAT eyes, and that young lady? Kinda Westworld. Cute, helpful, and completely lacking in personality. Did a self-deprecating joke in a complete monotone.  Seriously, she actually scared us a little.  I recommend this place, and it's ... Well, pretty darned good.
Fav spot in BK currently. Food is top notch. Wine is incredible! The staff is super helpful and super knowledgeable. Late not yakatori menu is pretty clutch too.
Great natural wines, knowledgeable and friendly staff.
Amazing drinks.
Every dish was on point. Scallops, ribs, snap peas all delicious.
Superbly classy and cool little restaurant...and also great for a coffee or a glass of wine

just had dinner and drinks with an old friend here. Highly recommend it. Very casual. It's a wine bar so I think it's a bit silly to just come here for the food. The food is meant to be shared and paired with the wine so it's best to order more than one plate. I got the $11/glass muscadet wine with the gnocchi. I honestly thought the food was better than the wine. It was perfect. Hope you enjoy it like I did :)
Love this place.  The food is exceptional and the service is knowledgeable and lovely.

I was lucky enough to get a seat at the window one busy Saturday evening. Very busy. The staff was great. Laid back, friendly, knowledgeable. Our server made a couple of recommendations and brought a white wine that totally blew my mind.  Even as busy as they were the staff was always available,  friendly and attentive.  Definitely a gem.

You know a place has good food and cheap drinks if it's hopping at 2 pm on a Saturday.  The menu is simple, but there's no shortage of tasty options.  Just know that it is more 'fried bologna and burgers' joint, and it has that authentic dive bar atmosphere.  Most sandwiches are $5-7 and come with chips.  I had a cheeseburger (Swiss) with grilled mushrooms and onions and tater tots. I think the burger was $7.25 and tots were $2.25.  The burger was greasy but in that good diner kind of way, and toys were crispy but I'd skip them next time.  Service was efficient though a little slow as it was packed.   She was booking it and friendly.  I want to go back to try their chunks, but I'll have to have a few weeks to recover.
Really great food and wines. The basil ice cream is amazing!
Standing room drinking until you can get a seat at the bar. Diners get tables. Small little restaurant with a single stall restroom. Cute decor. Good wine and staff.
Great staff
Good food in Brooklyn

Extraordinary wine bar with a very big list, The staff will help you navigate this huge list that has something for everybody. If you are looking a massive selection of your traditional wine, perhaps this place might disappoint you, but if you want to sample very good, well made wine, off the beaten track this place is for you. The small plates (did not have any mains this time) are super fresh packed with lots of flavour and character. Well worth a visit.
Absolutely love this place. Great wine list and the staff is pretty knowledgeable.
Great place for a quick drink
Great food.

Perfect place for a date. This place has an exceptional atmosphere, attentive staff, great wine selection and above all else exceptional food. The menu changes frequently with what is fresh and in season. Not to be missed is the homemade bread and one of the top tier desserts.  Pro tip: make a reservation if you can
Food is ok. Definitely not worth the hipe or the price. Wine-by-glass selection is ok but not spectacular.  Very claustrophobic.
Go here, the food is awesome and the wine selection is even better. It can get crowded but it's worth. Staff is nice and super knowledgable. Will keep going
Love this place, and let's be honest anything that J Murphy does! Simple, to the point and welcoming! Nice place to hang for any occasion!

This is one of our favorite places to go in New York.  The food is some of the best we have found.  If you like small places with over the top food then you will love The Four Horsemen.  Their wines are also the best natural wines you will find in the city.  Worth the drive from Manhattan.
Amazing vibe in a tight space. Service went above and beyond to make the night comfortable. Wine selection is not cheap, but it is fantastic. Liked everything I tried.
The vibe is smooth. Inviting and chic. The food is top notch. The wines are interesting and the service is where it needs to be to round out a good night with or without frills. Highly recommend.

We spent New Year's Eve here for 2015 and the food was incredible! We were brought out some very unique wines by our amazing server Will. He was very knowledgable and we just told him to bring out whatever he thought we'd like. We had the oysters and scallops to start, which were super fresh and had very unique flavors. The pasta was to die for and the meats were all delicious. Every dish seemed to melt in your mouth. The music and ambiance were just perfect! Not too loud. I will be back here next time I'm in Nyc!
Nice date spot
Amazing place. Cozy but modern interior, very nice staff and delicious selection of wine. I wish I had come to try their food too, but so happy I made it there.
Amazing natural wine selection, ingredient-led cooking... great vegetable dishes. This is the future of restaurants.
Scrumptious food and great vibe.
